@node Introduction
   
   This  program converts AmiNet INDEXs to the AmigaGuide© format, giving extra data
about its content (size, number of directories and subdirectories) in view of the
need to improve @{"Aminet2AG V1.1a" link VERSION1.1a}.
   
   The main features are the correction of failures in generating the
index and the capacity to deal with different index formats. For example:


	@{" INDEX Aminet           " link INDEX-EXAMPLE}

	@{" INDEX AmigaGuide© V2.0 " link GUIDE-EXAMPLE_Main}
	
	@{" INDEX AmigaGuide© V1.0a" link OLD-EXAMPLE_Main}

@endnode
	

@node SysReq "System Requirements"

Aminet2AG v2.0 requires:

   - AmigaOS Release 2.04 (V37+)
   
   - AmiNet index file.
   
   
   This program has been tested on the following machines:
   
     - A1200HD 68020 14MHz/No FPU, 2Mb Chip/0Mb Fast, AGA, Kick 3.0, WB 3.0
     - A2000HD 68000 28MHz/No FPU, 1Mb Chip/4Mb Fast, ECS, Kick 2.04, WB 2.1
     - A2000HD 68030 50MHz/68882 , 1Mb Chip/8Mb Fast, ECS, Kick 3.1, WB 3.1

   It does not produce any Enforcer hit.

@endnode

@node Installation
   - Simply copy the executable program to any place in your path, et voilŕ.
   
   - After this, take a postcard from the country where you live and send
     it to me 8^).
   
   ATTENTION!!!
    The last step is obligatory for the program to work properly  ;^D.

@endnode
			      
@node Usage

   A quick example that should be useful to almost any user is:

	 @{b}Aminet2AG @{"INDEX" link INDEX-EXAMPLE} @{"Aminet.guide" link GUIDE-EXAMPLE_Main} VERBOSE@{ub}
		   ^^^^^  ^^^^^^^^^^^
		     |         |
	  source index      destination index



   The program uses the following AmigaDOS command line:
   
@{b}FROMFILE/A,TOFILE/A,DC=DIRCOL/K/N,NT=NOTOTAL/S,NH=NOHEAD/S,NL=NOTITLE/S,
TR=TITLEROWS/K/N,NS=NOSTATS/S,SC=SIZECOL/K/N,P=PLAIN/S,V=VERBOSE/S@{ub}

   corresponding to the following in BNF notation:
   
   <from_file> <to_file> [ PLAIN | ( [ NOTOTAL ] [ NOHEAD ] [ NOTITLE ]
   [ NOHEAD ] ) [ TITLEROWS = <n> ] [ DIRCOL = <n> ] [ SIZECOL = <n> ]
   [ VERBOSE ]
   

   
   The options have the following meanings:

   
   @{b}FROMFILE/A@{ub}:
   ----------
      Name of the source AmiNet index file, from which the AmigaGuide© index
 will be constructed .
   
   
   @{b}TOFILE/A@{ub}:
   ---------
      Name of the destination index file in AmigaGuide© format.
      
      
   @{b}DC=DIRCOL/K/N@{ub}
   -------------
      Column number minus 1 where the directory name begins in the AmiNet index.
   
      It has a default value of 19.
   
   Example:
   
imdb3_1_bin.lha    gfx/dbase  240K   8+The Internet MovieDatabase Amiga 
		   ^
		   19                  
   
   @{b}NT=NOTOTAL/S@{ub}:
   ------------
      Deactivates the creation of total/partial lines in the
   directory/subdirectory nodes.
   
      The totals have the following format:
     .               .        .          .
     .               .        .          .
     .               .        .          .
   
  |  TEXT  |          8       480     > 72.5M 
  |  UTIL  |         22      1766     > 85.9M 
  ----------
                                                                           <
@{i}  Total:  15 dirs, 168 subdirs, 13100 files, size >  1.85G@{ui}                 <
                                                                           <
   
   @{b}NH=NOHEAD/S@{ub}:
   -----------
      Deactivates the heading creation. This option is
   automatic when the NOSTATS option is called.
   
      The heading has the following format:

@{i}                   subdirs    files      size@{ui}                              <
-------------------------------------------------------                    <
  ----------
  |  gfx   |          4       325     > 72.4M 
  |  gfx   |         15      1238     > 81.2M 
      .               .        .          .
      .               .        .          .
      .               .        .          .

   
   @{b}NL=NOTITLE/S@{ub}:
   ------------
      Deactivates title generation from the AmiNet site.

      The title consists of the first lines of the heading. The number of lines
 can be specified  with the TR=TITLEROW/K/N option.
   
      The title has the following format:
      
@{i}  Complete Aminet index on 28-Mar-95 
  The list is sorted by directory and file name    
  This site, ftp.netnet.net [198.70.64.3], contains all files of Aminet@{ui}
  
  
   @{b}TR=TITLEROWS/K/N@{ub}:
   ----------------
      Indicates the number of lines of the original index heading to be copied
   to the AmigaGuide© index title.
   
      By default it has the value of 3.
   
   @{b}NS=NOSTATS/S@{ub}:
   -------------
      Deactivates the statistics creation option of all
      directories/subdirectories.
   
      The statistics have the following format:
 
  ----------
  |  gfx   |          4       325     > 72.4M 
  |  dev   |         15      1238     = 81.2M 
      .               .        .          .
      .               .        .          .
      .               .        .          .
		 ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
				      ^
				      |
				      |-  = :  It knows the size of all the
				      |         files.
				      \\-  > :  It does not know the size of
				               some file(s).

   @{b}SC=SIZECOL/K/N@{ub}:
   ------------
      Column number minus 1 where the file size is located.
    [It is three places before the size indicator (K, M, ?)].
      
      By default it has the value of 30

   Example:
   
imdb3_1_bin.lha    gfx/dbase  240K   8+The Internet MovieDatabase Amiga 
			      ^
			      30

   @{b}P=PLAIN/S@{ub}:
   -------
      Activates the NOTITLE, NOHEAD, NOTOTAL, and NOSTATS options.
   I hope nobody will use this option.


   @{b}V=VERBOSE/S@{ub}:
   -----------
      Activates the generation of messages during the program execution.
   
@endnode

@node History

   @{" Version 1.1a " link VERSION1.1a} by Andre Lackmann.
   
   @{" Version 2.0  " link VERSION2.0}  by me.

@endnode

@node VERSION1.1a "Version 1.1a"
   
   @{i}Extracted from the original documentation by @{b}Andre Lackmann@{ub}@{ui}

     "Changed a few things, including the name (was called Short2AG, but the
     Aminet changed the name of the file. Is now called Aminet2AG).
     Fixed the 'nodes' so that they are all justified.
     Fixed our contact details (we moved)
     Still didn't comment the source."

@endnode

@node VERSION2.0 "Version 2.0"

   - 10 times faster!
   - Requires AmigaDOS 2.04+
   - Generation of totals.
   - Generation of headings.
   - Generation of titles.
   - Parameters for several INDEX types.
   - Command template in AmigaDOS format.
   - Executable size reduced to half.
   - Optimized code for Amiga working (No ANSI-C).
   - Documentation in AmigaGuide© format.

@endnode

@node Future

   - Localized. (There are some ideas floating around).
   
   - Integration of RECENTs in the index.
   
   - Generation of AmigaGuide© index from RECENTs.
   
   - Generation of RECENTs.
   
   - Other ideas...

@endnode Future


